{{Nihongo|'''''Ange Vierge'''''|アンジュ・ヴィエルジュ|Anju Vieruju}} is a Japanese [[digital collectible card game]] released by [[Fujimi Shobo]] and [[Media Factory]], two [[brand]] companies of [[Kadokawa Corporation]]. It was first announced in 2013. The franchise theme song is by L.I.N.K.s, a group composed of the voice actresses [[Yūka Aisaka]], [[Mai Ishihara]], [[Yoshiko Ikuta]], [[Rie Takahashi]], and [[Nozomi Yamamoto]].

A [[manga]] series titled ''Ange Vierge Linkage'' by Mako Komao with art by Sakaki Yoshioka was serialized in [[Fujimi Shobo]]'s ''[[shōnen manga|shōnen]]'' manga magazine ''[[Monthly Dragon Age]]'' between 2014 and 2015, and was collected in two ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes.

On April 20, 2017, Kadokawa announced that further development of the trading card game has been discontinued. A final tournament will take place in May 2017, with the franchise's tournaments and campaigns ending at the end of June 2017. The franchise's website will be shut down on March 31, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=【重要】TCG商品展開休止のお知らせ|url=https://ange-vierge.com/news/?id=710|publisher=[[Kadokawa Corporation]]|accessdate=April 21, 2017|date=April 20, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ange Vierge Trading Card Game Stops Development|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-20/ange-vierge-trading-card-game-stops-development/.115054|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=April 21, 2017|date=April 20, 2017}}</ref>

==Characters==

===Main characters===
;{{nihongo4|Saya Sōgetsu|蒼月紗夜|Sōgetsu Saya}}
:{{voiced by|[[Minako Kotobuki]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:A former high school student from the Blue World and the main protagonist. Though she is emotional, she is also brave and supportive when the situation calls for it. Before gaining her powers she was a completely normal high school student who barely had any kind of presence. She uses a lightsword in combat. The blue world is earth.

;{{nihongo4|Almaria|アルマリア|Arumaria}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yumi Hara]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:A mature vampire girl from the Black World. She fights using blood but at the same time she thinks that feeding on others is embarrassing, and thus has not bitten anyone yet. However, after drinking Saya's blood in a desperate situation, she becomes completely attached to her and is able to use her full powers.

;{{nihongo4|Elel|エルエル|Erueru}}
:{{voiced by|[[Aki Toyosaki]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:An extremely friendly and energetic angel from the Red World. She is able to become friends with anyone. Her ability is to borrow abilities from her friends, but it only works if there is a mutual bond between them.

;{{nihongo4|Code Omega 77 Stella|コードΩ77ステラ|Kōdo Ō 77 Sutera}}
:{{voiced by|[[Rika Tachibana]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:A [[Heterochromia iridum|heterochromic]] android from the White World. She has a passion for speed and wants to become even faster than before. Her ability is to manipulate acceleration.

;{{nihongo4|Nya Lapucea|ナイア・ラピュセア|Naia Rapyusea}}
:{{voiced by|[[Sarah Emi Bridcutt]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:A busty and mature girl from the Green World. She has the reflexes of a soldier (as she is an ex-squad leader) but is also quite carefree and hates trouble. She is also very lazy, always trying to find excuses to avoid working. She feels guilty for what happened to Eins, as she was the one leader of her squad during the time the accident happened.

;{{nihongo4|Amane Ayashiro|彩城天音|Ayashiro Amane}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yukari Tamura]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:The alpha-driver for Saya's team from the Blue World. Extremely clumsy and goofy yet also kindhearted and optimistic, Amane is the central point for the girls' motives, and each of their episodes shows just how they met and become friends with her. She loves teasing her friends, but is also easily hurt despite her carefree attitude. After episode 3, she is sealed within a crystal made by the Ouroboros.

===Other characters===

;{{nihongo4|Miumi Hinata|日向美海|Hinata Miumi}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yūka Aisaka]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:Saya's upperclassman and one of the strongest fighters in the academy.

;{{nihongo4|Sofina|ソフィーナ|Sofīna}}
:{{voiced by|[[Mai Ishihara]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:Almaria's upperclassman from the Black World. She likes teasing Almaria for the fact that she thinks that sucking blood is a very embarrassing act.

;{{nihongo4|Ruby|ルビー|Rubī}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yoshiko Ikuta]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:A fairy from the Red World.

;{{nihongo4|Code Omega 00 Yufiria|コードΩ00ユーフィリ|Kōdo Omega 00 Yūfiria}}
:{{voiced by|[[Rie Takahashi]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:An android from the White World.

;{{nihongo4|Mayuka Sanagi|マユカ・サナギ|Mayuka Sanagi}}
:{{voiced by|[[Nozomi Yamamoto]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:A soldier from the Green World. She is the younger sister of Ageha who is quite airheaded and a bit immature but loves her sister very much. Unlike her sister, she is lazy and hates work.

;{{nihongo4|Aoi Mikage|御影葵|Mikage Aoi}}
:{{voiced by|[[Shizuka Itō]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:Saya's upperclassman from the Blue World. She is a samurai-like girl who has mastered the ways of swordsmanship, and is quite strict towards her underclassmen.

;{{nihongo4|Ramiel|レミエル|Remieru}}
:{{voiced by|[[Aoi Yūki]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:Elel's upperclassman and an angel as well. Though she has only one wing and can't use her other eye as well, she is extremely kind and optimistic.

;{{nihongo4|Code Omega 33 Carene||コードΩ33カレン|Kōdo Omega 33 Karen}}
:{{voiced by|[[Minori Chihara]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:Stella's upperclassman. She adores her younger sister, Xenia, more than anything.

;{{nihongo4|Code Omega 46 Senia|コードΩ46セニア|Kōdo Omega 46 Senia}}
:{{voiced by|[[Kana Hanazawa]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:Carene's younger sister and an android taking a little girl's form. She is also Yufiria's mother.

;{{nihongo4|Eins Exaura|アインス・エクスアウラ|Ainsu ekusuaura}}
:{{voiced by|[[Ayane Sakura]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:An enhanced soldier, Expend, from the Green World and a top-rated soldier. She always has an emotionless look on her face and talks in monotone, but is quite arrogant and loves thinking about the world's destruction and just destruction in general. She used to be an energetic and hardworking rookie in Nya's squad until she had to be abandoned and was then modified even more, resulting her in becoming what she is now.

;{{nihongo4|Ageha Sanagi|アゲハ・サナギ|Ageha Sanagi}}
:{{voiced by|[[Sumire Uesaka]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}
:Mayuka's older sister and though she is serious and acts like a drill sergeant towards her, she is shown to love her very much.

;{{nihongo4|Aurora|アウロラ|Aurora}}
:{{voiced by|[[Saori Hayami]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}

;{{nihongo4|Dr. Michael|Dr.ミハイル|Dr. Mihairu}}
:{{voiced by|[[Mai Aizawa (voice actress)|Mai Aizawa]]<ref name="ann-103420"/>}}

;{{nihongo4|Clara|クララ|Kurara}}
:{{voiced by|[[Saya Satō]]<ref name="ann-103420">{{cite web|title=Ange Vierge Anime Adds More Cast|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-06-20/ange-vierge-anime-adds-more-cast/.103420|accessdate=June 26, 2016}}</ref>}}

==Media==

===Anime===
An [[anime]] television series adaptation by [[Silver Link]] aired from July<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-12-06/ange-vierge-trading-card-game-gets-anime-project/.81839|title=''Ange Vierge'' Trading Card Game Gets Anime Project|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 6, 2014|accessdate=December 6, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-06/ange-vierge-anime-silver-link-studio-2016-debut-visuals-unveiled/.96165|title=''Ange Vierge'' Anime's Silver Link Studio, 2016 Debut, Visuals Unveiled|publisher=Anime News Network|date=December 6, 2015|accessdate=December 6, 2015}}</ref><ref name="song">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-05-16/ange-vierge-tv-anime-reveals-staff-theme-songs-more-cast/.102175|title=Ange Vierge TV Anime Reveals Staff, Theme Songs, More Cast|date=May 16, 2016|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=May 16, 2016}}</ref> to September 2016. [[Crunchyroll]] streamed the anime on its website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-07-04/crunchyroll-to-stream-ange-vierge-fate-kaleid-liner-prisma-illya-3rei-anime/.103965|title=Crunchyroll to stream Ange Vierge, Fate Kaleid Liner Prisma Illya 3rei anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=July 4, 2016|accessdate=July 4, 2016}}</ref> The opening theme is "Love is My Rail" by [[Konomi Suzuki]], and the ending theme is "Link with U" by L.I.N.K.s ([[Yūka Aisaka]], [[Mai Ishihara]], [[Yoshiko Ikuta]], [[Rie Takahashi]], and [[Nozomi Yamamoto]])<ref name="song"/>

