'''Planetarium software''' is [[application software]] that allows a user to simulate the [[celestial sphere]] at any time of day, especially at [[night sky|night]], on a computer. Such applications can be as rudimentary as displaying a [[star chart]] or [[star cartography|sky map]] for a specific time and location, or as complex as [[rendering (computer graphics)|rendering photorealistic]] views of the [[sky]].
While some planetarium software is meant to be used exclusively on a personal computer, some applications can be used to interface with and [[GoTo (telescopes)|control telescopes]] or [[planetarium projector]]s. Optional features may include inserting the [[orbital elements]] of comets and other newly discovered bodies for display.
==Packages== {{Div col|colwidth=15em}} * [[C2A Planetarium Software]] * [[Cartes du Ciel]] * [[Celestia]] * [[CyberSky]] * [[Digital Universe Atlas]] * [[Nightshade (astronomy software)|Nightshade]] * [[Google Sky]] * [[Sky Map]] * [[SkyMap Pro]] by Chris Marriott * [[HNSKY]] * [[KStars]] * [[RedShift (planetarium software)|RedShift]] * [[TheSky (astronomy software)|TheSky]] * [[Starry Night (planetarium software)|Starry Night]] * [[Stellarium (software)|Stellarium]] * [[XEphem]] * [[SpaceEngine]] * [[WinStars]] * [[WorldWide Telescope]] * [[Sciss]] * [[Digital Sky 2]]{{Div col end}}
