{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2015}} {{Infobox company | name = Rabbit Bandini Productions | type = Private | logo = | slogan = | foundation = 2003 | location = [[Burbank, California|Burbank, CA]] | key_people = {{Plainlist| * [[James Franco]] * Vince Jolivette}} | num_employees = | industry = Film }}
'''Rabbit Bandini Productions''' is a film production company founded in 2003 by actors/filmmakers [[James Franco]] and Vince Jolivette. The name comes from combining the titular hero from [[John Updike]]'s Rabbit tetralogy with the hero of [[John Fante]]'s ''[[Ask the Dust]]'', Arturo Bandini.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://filmschoolrejects.com/james-franco-books-and-films-fa43bacd8875|title=What is James Franco Reading?|date=April 13, 2017|publisher=}}</ref>
==Works== Recent credits include director [[Gia Coppola]]'s drama [[Palo Alto (2013 film)|Palo Alto]] and Franco's directorial adaptations of Pulitzer Prize-winning author [[Cormac McCarthy]]'s [[Child of God]] and Nobel Prize-winning author [[William Faulkner]]'s [[As I Lay Dying (film)|As I Lay Dying]] and [[The Sound and the Fury (2014 film)|The Sound and The Fury]] premiering at the 2014 [[Venice Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/09/james-franco-sound-and-the-fury-venice-film-festival-exclusive-video-827503/|title=Hot Venice Clip: James Franco’s ‘The Sound And The Fury’|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=September 1, 2014|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref>
Rabbit Bandini Productions has multiple projects in various stages of development. In production, ''[[In Dubious Battle (film)|In Dubious Battle]]'', based on the [[John Steinbeck|Steinbeck]] book of the same name.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/james-franco-assembles-cast-for-john-steinbeck-adaptation-of-john-steinbeck-in-dubious-battle-1201419696/|title=James Franco Assembles Cast for Adaptation of ‘In Dubious Battle’|first=Justin|last=Kroll|date=January 30, 2015|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref> ''[[The Adderall Diaries (film)|The Adderall Diaries]]'' directed by [[Pamela Romanowsky]], starring [[James Franco|Franco]], [[Ed Harris]], [[Amber Heard]] and [[Christian Slater]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tribecafilm.com/filmguide/adderall-diaries-2015|title=The Adderall Diaries - Tribeca Film Festival|website=Tribeca}}</ref>
Completed in 2015 was Justin Kelly's directorial adaptation of the biopic ''[[I Am Michael]]'', with Franco, [[Zachary Quinto]] and [[Emma Roberts]] and ''[[Zeroville (film)|Zeroville]]'' directed by Franco, starring [[Megan Fox]], [[Seth Rogen]] and [[Will Ferrell]] along with [[James Franco|Franco]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/sundance-film-review-james-franco-in-i-am-michael-1201414176/|title=Sundance Film Review: ‘I Am Michael’|first=Peter|last=Debruge|date=January 25, 2015|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2014/10/24/casting-net-megan-fox-james-franco-zeroville|title=Casting Net: Megan Fox, James Franco lead 'Zeroville'|date=October 24, 2014|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref> The company teamed up with [[Seth Rogen]] and [[Evan Goldberg]] on [[The Disaster Artist (film)|The Disaster Artist]], which is financed by Good Universe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1722035/james-franco-the-room/|title=James Franco Plans To Enter 'The Room' With Behind-The-Scenes Movie|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref> In 2015, the company also produced "Actors Anonymous",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4577974/?ref_=nv_sr_1|title=Actors Anonymous|date=January 1, 2000|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2017|via=IMDb}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ireport.cnn.com/docs/DOC-1264944|publisher=|accessdate=January 10, 2017}}</ref> a film funded by [[Sara Von Kienegger]], in conjunction with students and the USC Film School.
